        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 4:20PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 420 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles east of Ski Bluewood, or 24 miles southeast of Dayton, moving
north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Columbia County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
